.TH PASSWD 1
.SH NAME
passwd \- Sets users password
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B passwd
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.I passwd
command prompts for a password and prints an encrypted hash to the terminal
.SH FILES
/etc/passwd
.SH "SEE ALSO"
passwd(5)
.SH BUGS
The encrypted password should be written to /etc/passwd, not just printed to
the terminal. An optional user name should be accepted as argument, and the
password of that user should be changed. passwd should prompt for the password
twice, and only accept it if they match.